  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and roughly chop your <strong>shallot[s] </strong>and <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and roughly chop your <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Bash your<strong> lemongrass stalk[s] </strong>with a <strong>rolling pin</strong>, remove the <strong>tough outer layers </strong>and<strong> </strong>set aside for later, then chop the<strong> softer inner core[s]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span></strong>roughly</p><p>Chop your <strong>coriander</strong> roughly, including the stalks</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1614619905626-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1614619905626-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1614619905626-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1614619905626-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1614619905626-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped shallot</strong>, <strong>garlic</strong>, <strong>ginger</strong>,<strong> chopped lemongrass </strong>and <strong>coriander </strong>to a <strong>food processor</strong> with your<strong> ground paprika</strong>, <strong>cracked black pepper</strong>,<strong> chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and<strong> soy sauce</strong></p><p>Add 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [4 tbsp]<strong> </span>vegetable oil</strong>, 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> and 1 1/2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[2 1/4 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[3 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar </strong>and blitz to a paste – this is your<strong> fiery curry paste</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1614619921454-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1614619921454-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1614619921454-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1614619921454-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1614619921454-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>white long grain</strong> <strong>rice </strong>to a pot with 225ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[300ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [450ml]</span> <strong>cold water </strong>and the <strong>outer</strong> <strong>lemongrass layers </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to low and stir vigorously for 1 min, then cover and cook for 12-15 min or until the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, remove the pot from the heat and discard the <strong>outer lemongrass layers</strong> – this is your<strong> lemongrass rice</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1614619937983-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1614619937983-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1614619937983-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1614619937983-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1614619937983-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the rice is cooking, drain your<strong> tofu</strong> and pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Cut the<strong> tofu</strong> in half lengthways, then slice into 8<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>pieces per person</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a very generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a high heat</p><p>Once very hot, add the <strong>tofu pieces </strong>with a generous pinch<strong> </strong>of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 4-5 min, turning once halfway until golden and crisp</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1614619949826-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1614619949826-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1614619949826-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1614619949826-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1614619949826-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, trim, then chop your <strong>green beans</strong> in half</p><p>Peel and chop your<strong> red onion[s]</strong> into wedges</p><p>Separate the<strong> onion wedges</strong> into petals</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1614619964029-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1614619964029-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1614619964029-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1614619964029-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1614619964029-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the tofu<strong> </strong>is golden and crisp, transfer it to kitchen paper<strong> </strong>and return the pan to a medium heat</p><p>Add the <strong>halved green beans</strong> and<strong> onion petals</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until starting to soften and lightly blister</p><p>Tip: Add a drizzle more oil if your pan is looking a little dry!</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1614619976100-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1614619976100-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1614619976100-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1614619976100-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1614619976100-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>fiery curry paste</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until fragrant, then return the <strong>crispy tofu </strong>to the pan</p><p>Cook for 2 min further, stirring to coat everything in the paste – this is your <strong>tofu pad prik king</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1614620016102-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
